      • _fromImpl

        public static ChemicalBuilder _fromImpl(ChemicalImpl impl)
        Utility method for SPIs to easily create a Chemical from the SPI implementation object. This method should not be used by end users and is only exposed as a public method due to java visibility limitations. ONLY USE IF YOU ARE AN SPI
        Parameters:
        impl - the ChemicalImpl to wrap for this builder.
        Returns:
        a new Builder instance.

      • addAtom

        public Atom addAtom(String symbol,
                    double x,
                    double y,
                    double z)
        Add a new atom to this molecule with the given element symbol and the given coordinates.

        This is the same as : 

         Atom a = addAtom(symbol);
 a.setLocation(x, y, z);
 return a;
        Parameters:
        symbol - the elemental symbol of the atom; can not be null.
        x - the x coordinate.
        y - the y coordinate.
        z - the z coordinate.
        Returns:
        the new Atom that was created.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if symbol is null.

        Returns:

        Throws:
